(b) The healthcare insurer, pharmacy benefits manager, or other
interested party shall provide a notice of seven (7) days to the Arkansas
State Board of Pharmacy and the Arkansas State Medical Board of the
healthcare insurer's, pharmacy benefits manager's, or other interested
party's intent to file an appeal.
(c) No later than the thirtieth day after the date a healthcare
insurer, pharmacy benefits manager, or other interested party files an appeal
under subsection (a) of this section, the Insurance Commissioner shall
appoint an independent review organization to review the appeal.
(c)(d) A healthcare insurer, pharmacy benefits manager, or other
interested party that files an appeal under subsection (a) of this section
shall pay for the independent review organization appointed under subsection
(b)(c) of this section to review the appeal.
